<ul><li>The&nbsp;<b>density of a gas is much less</b>&nbsp;than the density of the same substance in liquid or solid state.</li><li>This is because molecules of a solid and liquid are&nbsp;<b>packed together in contact</b>&nbsp;with each other.</li><li>Whereas molecules of a gas are on average&nbsp;<b>separated from each other</b>&nbsp;by relatively large distances.</li></ul>